                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know there has been a thread about this, but I wanted to make sure that the info was current, and had not been changed in the last few patches...
<br />

<br />
For the Plane of Justice Execution Trial... will Dire Charmed pets teleport with you to the trial, or not? And the mobs within the trial are charmable with Beckon, correct?
<br />

<br />

<br />
I have a normal group that I travel with, and we're very good at our classes, but a little short on DPS. I know that the "normal" way to beat the Execution trial is all about AE (nukes, stuns, tash). Is it possible that a charmed pet will add enough DPS to a group to simply mow through the mobs in a more traditional fashion?
<br />

<br />
My group consists of a WAR, CLR, ENC, SHM, SHD, and a friend who normally plays a second cleric  can brink a MNK. Average level about 62.
<br />

<br />
The way I see it, we don't have that much to lose, even if we fail. Anyone have any tips on how we might be able to accomplish this? If DC is the way to go, what are the good mobs in PoJ to get?
<br />

<br />
Thanks very much for your help, I have been reading the messages for some time, and have learned a lot... but this is the first time I have actually posted.
<br />

<br />

<br />
-- Maruq, 62 ENC</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
