                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have never done it AE style.
<br />

<br />
I didn't know that was the 'normal' way.
<br />

<br />
I have found charm very helpful in exe (and all) of the trials.  They are in fact charmable with Boltran's Agacerie.  The razorfiends.  Rocks might be charmable with a higher spell, yes.
<br />

<br />
What I do -- everyone but the MT stands in the corner behind the scaffolding (either one).  MT sits right between the front two pews, garaunteeing aggro once they spawn.  After about a 3 count, I cast AE tash centered on the MT.  (When I was lower level and had fewer hp, I cast single tash on my intended charm target instead.) I then charm a fiend, and sick it on the MT's mob.
<br />

<br />
Now I look to mez any remaining fiends.
<br />

<br />
And from there, it's like a normal group fight, really.  Everyone stick close together so that no one has to chase a mob down.
<br />

<br />
Your group at level 62 may have some trouble with DPS, depending on how well you are geareed.  But as you said, may as well go for it.
<br />

<br />
Some of the other trials may be better for that group, stoning and hanging in particular.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Eleandra
<br />
<a href="http://www.scienceofwar.net" target="_blank">www.scienceofwar.net</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
