                                <td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=11631&amp;sid=36da899b13feda856a1102af9438df44#11631"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Fri Dec 05, 2003 11:56 am<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: Execution Trial</span></td>
                                <td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=11631&amp;sid=36da899b13feda856a1102af9438df44"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">We used to have trouble doing this trial til someone posted a while back that they had changed it to make pets follow. Of course I decided to try it by myself just to prove that it works. So I charmed a wandering guard ran into the trial and sure enough he followed. Charm broke shortly after so I kited around until the prisoner was dead and 'return'ed. 
<br />

<br />
Once I knew that it worked, I started Pacifying one of the BIG guards to the port up area (up the stairs by the door). Bliss his partner, tell the group to be ready, tash, charm, and wait for bliss to break. 
<br />

<br />
I mezzed him because down stairs he has 4 buddies and the genie guy and a wanderer just outside the room so I don't want him moving angry. 
<br />

<br />
When Bliss breaks I run back up trhough the portal and have my pet guard, back up, break charm and have the ranger/druid/sk/necro snare (assuming you have one) and/or the Shaman Malo. Recharm, and begin the trial. 
<br />

<br />
Once inside have your MA/tank sit in the middle between all the seats. 
<br />

<br />
I prefer chain stuns so I have the MA clear his target window, and when the mobs pop, whomever hits him is your first target. Assist and send the pet in, AOE Tash, go stand next to the MA and chain stun as if your life depends on it (Because it does). 
<br />

<br />
When the first mob dies, instead of having everyone assist the MA, have them assist your pet. By now you have been hit by all the remaining mobs (due to the AOE Tash and stuns) and your pet is ready to kill them all. The pet does serious damage and we usually kill each mob in about 15 seconds. Your pet can solo one in 30 seconds so if he switches targets you still shouldn't have any trouble. 
<br />

<br />
When there all dead, re-rune and do it again. 
<br />

<br />
At the end of the 3rd wave BREAK CHARM. At full duration, with the pauses between waves, it's likely that he will break by himself sometime during the 4th wave, so your better breaking it yourself and redoing it now. Run to a corner, recharm and get ready for the next wave. If he breaks during a fight, keep chain stunning, when you get to your last stun in the cycle (which should be your longest lasting stun) assuming you got no resist messages, charm him again.
<br />

<br />
Near the end of the 4th wave, have all of your people get off the stage (where they have been starting every wave so far to avoid agro, right?) and move to a back corner or back wall. When the named spawns he won't have any agro and will kill the low hp guys on stage where he spawns unless your MA is quick. 
<br />

<br />
Slow him and kill him. Have the pet guard at the opposite end of the trial while you get your marks, 'return', and then either kill your pet or have those who debuffed him, along with yourself, camp out.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
