                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Trial of Torment
<br />

<br />
We had a guild group messing around and seeing if we could find a way to get people flagged through trials so we were practicing. Well after a few runs thru executioner trial we were trying to decide what to do next. I read thru all the trial descriptions on Allakhazam and we decided to do Torment.
<br />

<br />
Well it's hard to be sure because this was a good group that stomped executioner trials, but Trial of Torment seems to be just as easy, if not easier. 
<br />
You must kill 4 waves of mobs, then a boss much like the executioner trial. The shades are mezzable but the razorfiends(aliens) are not. There is no timer to complete this trial, but the waves of mobs spawn whether or not you have finished off the last wave. The interesting thing is that if you finish off a wave of mobs before the next spawns, an extra mob spawns, and an AE heal goes off when you kill this extra mob. The strategy that I read and that we used tho, we simply kept a shade mezzed throughout the whole trial, and never encountered an extra mob. I remember at least 1 wave was all the unmezzable razorfiends, but I AE'd Tash and stunned like I normally do on executioner and with a good cleric and tank we were fine. Also the boss at the end will not spawn til all mobs are killed, so I kept the shade mezzed until we had medded up and were more than ready to fight the executioner mob.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
